// C3: Physical Sensing Components
instance CranePositionSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensors measuring the physical position of the gantry crane components (e.g., horizontal/vertical displacement)."
    DTDFVocab:producedData CranePositionDataTransmitted
]

instance CraneVelocitySensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensors measuring the velocity of the gantry crane components (e.g., puck and gantry movement speed)."
    DTDFVocab:producedData CraneVelocityDataTransmitted
]

instance CraneAccelerationSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensors measuring the acceleration of the gantry crane components (e.g., dynamic forces during movement)."
    DTDFVocab:producedData CraneAccelerationDataTransmitted
]

instance ControllerFeedbackSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensors capturing feedback from the crane controller (e.g., control signals, error corrections)."
    DTDFVocab:producedData ControllerFeedbackDataTransmitted
]

instance LoadWeightSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensors measuring the weight of the load being transported by the crane."
    DTDFVocab:producedData LoadWeightDataTransmitted
]

instance EnvironmentalFactorSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Sensors capturing environmental factors affecting crane operation (e.g., ambient conditions)."
    DTDFVocab:producedData EnvironmentalFactorDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Physical-to-Virtual Interaction
instance CranePositionDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom CranePositionSensor
]

instance CraneVelocityDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom CraneVelocitySensor
]

instance CraneAccelerationDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom CraneAccelerationSensor
]

instance ControllerFeedbackDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom ControllerFeedbackSensor
]

instance LoadWeightDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom LoadWeightSensor
]

instance EnvironmentalFactorDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom EnvironmentalFactorSensor
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance CraneKinematicModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Mathematical representation of the crane's movement mechanics enabling simulation and control."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo KinematicSimulationEnabler
]

instance CraneStateData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Aggregated operational data from the physical crane including position, velocity, acceleration, and controller feedback."
    DTDFVocab:fromData CranePositionDataTransmitted, CraneVelocityDataTransmitted, CraneAccelerationDataTransmitted, ControllerFeedbackDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo HistoricalDataStorageEnabler, ContinuousValidationEnabler
]

instance SimulatedTrajectoryData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Digitally generated trajectory data for comparison with physical crane movements."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo ContinuousValidationEnabler
]

instance HistoricalCraneData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Long-term operational and sensor data stored for analysis and validation."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo HistoricalDataLoggingService
]

// C11: Enablers
instance KinematicSimulationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Software platform enabling mathematical simulation of crane kinematics (e.g., MATLAB/Simulink, Python with SymPy)."
    DTDFVocab:enables OptimalControlService, DataVisualizationService
]

instance HistoricalDataStorageEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Database system for storing operational and sensor data (e.g., TimescaleDB, SQL/NoSQL databases)."
    DTDFVocab:enables HistoricalDataLoggingService, FaultDetectionService
]

instance ContinuousValidationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Service ensuring synchronization between physical and digital crane states via real-time validation."
    DTDFVocab:enables ContinuousValidationService
]

instance DigitalTwinFrameworkEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Framework enabling bidirectional data flow between physical and digital crane systems (e.g., custom-built or NVIDIA Omniverse)."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataVisualizationService, FaultDetectionService
]

instance OpenSourceDevelopmentEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Open-source software stack ensuring reproducibility (e.g., Python, ROS)."
    DTDFVocab:enables OptimalControlService, ContinuousValidationService
]

// C6: Services
instance OptimalControlService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service providing algorithms for optimizing crane control parameters (e.g., trajectory planning, energy efficiency)."
    DTDFVocab:provides OptimalTrajectoryInsight, EnergyEfficiencyAction
]

instance HistoricalDataLoggingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service collecting and storing operational data from the physical crane for analysis."
    DTDFVocab:provides CranePerformanceInsight
]

instance DataVisualizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service visualizing real-time and historical crane performance data."
    DTDFVocab:provides RealTimeMonitoringInsight, KinematicModelVisualizationInsight
]

instance ContinuousValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service validating digital twin accuracy by comparing digital and physical states."
    DTDFVocab:provides SynchronizationCheckInsight, FaultDetectionAction
]

instance FaultDetectionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service monitoring the system for anomalies or faults."
    DTDFVocab:provides AnomalyDetectionInsight, PredictiveMaintenanceAction
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance OptimalTrajectoryInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight providing optimized trajectory paths for crane movements."
]

instance EnergyEfficiencyAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Action enabling real-time adjustment of control parameters for energy efficiency."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance CranePerformanceInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight derived from historical operational data for trend analysis."
]

instance RealTimeMonitoringInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight enabling real-time visualization of crane operational states."
]

instance KinematicModelVisualizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight visualizing the kinematic model and operational states of the crane."
]

instance SynchronizationCheckInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight validating synchronization between physical and digital crane states."
]

instance FaultDetectionAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Action alerting users to potential system issues based on anomaly detection."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance AnomalyDetectionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight identifying anomalies in operational data for predictive maintenance."
]

instance PredictiveMaintenanceAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Action triggering maintenance alerts based on detected anomalies."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

// C1: System Under Study
instance LabScaleGantryCrane : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "A small-scale mechanical gantry crane system used for research and validation of digital twin methodologies."
]

instance CraneController : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Embedded or software-based system responsible for controlling the crane's movements and operations."
]

instance LabEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Controlled indoor environment for the lab-scale gantry crane system."
    base:contains LabScaleGantryCrane, CraneController
]

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "The **Virtual-to-Physical Interaction** in this system is mediated by the **Control Application**, which generates and transmits control commands to the **Physical Crane** via the **Physical Crane Interface**. The **command types** include **optimal movement trajectories** (generated by the **Trajectory Generator Service**) with no residual swinging motion at the end. The **control message format** is not explicitly defined, but the system implies structured commands aligned with the crane’s kinematics model. **Validation and authentication mechanisms** are not explicitly described, though the **Continuous Validation Service** ensures executed trajectories match simulations, indirectly validating command execution. **Feedback systems** are present via the **Logging Application**, which captures real-time crane state data post-command execution. **Conflict resolution** is not detailed, but the **Dashboard** notifies operators if thresholds are breached, allowing manual intervention. **Command execution confirmation** is implied through the **Continuous Validation Service**, which compares executed trajectories against simulations and triggers alerts if discrepancies exceed thresholds."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin constellation in the provided exemplars follows an **ad-hoc, lightweight orchestration pattern** without reliance on commercial frameworks. The **GreenhouseDT** exemplar uses **InfluxDB** (time-series database) and **ActiveMQ** (message broker) to manage **behavioral adaptation** between the physical greenhouse and its Digital Twin, with **virtual machines** hosting pre-recorded data for offline analysis. The **Air Quality Management** exemplar employs **AutomationML** for Digital Twin modeling and **Microsoft Azure tools** for pipeline implementation, indicating a **cloud-centric, service-oriented constellation** with **three distinct applications** (runtime visualization, simulation, prediction) coordinated via Azure’s ecosystem. The **gantry crane system** (logistics domain) adopts a **C4 Model architecture**, emphasizing **context and container diagrams** for software-hardware integration but lacks explicit details on system-wide coordination mechanisms. **Containerization/virtualization** (e.g., Docker, VMs) is a recurring theme for **modular deployment**, while **single-board computers (Raspberry Pi)** serve as edge nodes for sensor-data acquisition. No formal orchestration framework (e.g., Kubernetes, service mesh) is mentioned; coordination relies on **ad-hoc integration** of components."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "The **GreenhouseDT** exemplar emphasizes **self-adaptive behavioral fidelity**, where both the physical greenhouse and its digital twin dynamically adjust to maintain synchronization. Validation is implied through **prerecorded data** in virtual machines, enabling offline testing of model accuracy against historical system behavior. The **Air Quality Management** exemplar focuses on **runtime validation** via three applications: **visualization** (real-time monitoring), **simulation** (scenario testing), and **prediction** (forecasting virus spread risks). Uncertainty quantification is not explicitly addressed, but the use of **Microsoft Azure tools** suggests cloud-based analytics for error detection (e.g., anomaly detection in sensor data). No formal **verification methods** (e.g., model checking, calibration protocols) or **quality assurance processes** are detailed, though the **ad-hoc architecture** implies iterative refinement based on empirical feedback. The **AutomationML** standard in the Air Quality exemplar may inherently support fidelity through structured model exchange, but no quantitative metrics (e.g., RMSE, confidence intervals) are provided."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The **Digital Twin’s Technical Connection** relies on a **service-oriented architecture** with the following key elements: **Communication protocols** include **MQTT** for inter-service signaling (via the **MQTT Broker**) and unspecified protocols for data transmission between the **Physical Crane Interface** and **Logging Application**. The **network topology** is not explicitly detailed, but the system implies a **centralized architecture** with the **Database (TimescaleDB)** as the core data repository. **Bandwidth and latency requirements** are not quantified, but the **Continuous Validation Service** suggests low-latency communication to enable real-time trajectory comparison. **Reliability and redundancy mechanisms** are not described, though the **MQTT Broker** and **Database** imply fault-tolerant design. **Security protocols** are not mentioned, but the system’s reliance on **TimescaleDB** and **Grafana Dashboard** suggests standard database and web security measures (e.g., authentication, encryption) are assumed."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The **Digital Twin’s Hosting and Deployment** infrastructure is not explicitly detailed in terms of cloud/edge/on-premise, but the system’s components suggest a **hybrid or on-premise deployment model**. The **Database (TimescaleDB)** and **MQTT Broker** imply **local hosting** for low-latency operations, while the **Dashboard (Grafana)** and **Simulation/Trajectory Services** may leverage **edge computing** for real-time processing. **Computational requirements** are not quantified, but the **Trajectory Generator Service** and **Simulation Service** require sufficient CPU/GPU resources for kinematics modeling and trajectory optimization. **Storage requirements** are met by **TimescaleDB**, which handles time-series data efficiently. **Scalability mechanisms** are not described, though the modular design (e.g., separate services) allows for potential horizontal scaling. **Availability/reliability assurance** is implied by the **Continuous Validation Service** and **Dashboard alerts**, but no explicit redundancy or failover strategies are mentioned."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin systems exhibit **limited but domain-specific horizontal integration** with external systems. The **GreenhouseDT** exemplar integrates with **InfluxDB** (for time-series data storage) and **ActiveMQ** (for message brokering), but no external interoperability standards (e.g., OPC UA, MQTT) or enterprise system dependencies are documented. The **Air Quality Management** exemplar uses **AutomationML** for Digital Twin modeling and **Microsoft Azure tools** (e.g., Azure IoT, Logic Apps) for pipeline orchestration, implying **cloud-based integration** with potential enterprise systems via Azure’s native protocols (e.g., REST APIs, event grids). The **gantry crane system** (logistics domain) lacks explicit details on external integration but aligns with **cyber-physical system (CPS) architectures**, which typically rely on **industrial protocols** (e.g., OPC UA, PROFINET) for factory/warehouse integration. No cross-Digital Twin or enterprise system interoperability (e.g., federated twins, shared ontologies) is described; integration patterns are **domain-isolated** and **ad-hoc**, with no standardized protocols for data exchange between twins."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The **Air Quality Management** exemplar adheres to **AutomationML** for digital twin modeling, a standardized format for engineering data exchange, ensuring interoperability with other industrial systems. The **GreenhouseDT** exemplar does not explicitly mention compliance with industry standards but relies on **commonly used technologies** (InfluxDB, ActiveMQ) that are widely adopted in IoT and cyber-physical systems. Neither exemplar references **certification requirements** or **compliance frameworks** (e.g., ISO 22400 for digital twins, IEC 62443 for cybersecurity). The **lab-scale gantry crane** exemplar does not provide details on standardization, though its architecture is visualized using the **C4 Model**, a software-centric notation. **Interoperability standards** are only explicitly mentioned for AutomationML in the Air Quality Management case."
]